      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PRESTIGE GUNDY (4) progressed nicely last time out at the second run of the campaign when he made late ground to finish less than a length away from the winner at Ipswich. At his top now and can find winning ways. HERALD ANGEL (8) drifted well back when resuming last start before winding up strongly to just miss when second over 1010m at Murwillumbah. Strips fitter and will appreciate the added trip. SCOUNDREL (5) didn't fire a shot fresh when tackling much tougher company at Doomben. Much better placed dropping back to this level and should improve with that run under his belt. HE'S A COPY BOY (7) caught the eye late when resuming at Grafton. Better for that and is among the better hopes.",
